2026-07-16 (0.3.0):
    Important: Delete existing Virtual Service and VMware Avi Special Agent rules before upgrading and recreate them after installing version 0.3.0
    Added Pool monitoring including operational state, health scores, server status, alerts and performance metrics
    Added a preconfigured Avi Load Balancer dashboard
    Added a required Avi API version option, HTTP POST support and support for the Avi analytics metric collection API
    Reworked Virtual Service metric collection and added detailed namespaced response time, connection, throughput, request and error metrics
    Added assigned and requested Service Engine details, associated Pool counts and handling for CLUSTER_UP_HA_NOT_READY, CLUSTER_UP_HA_COMPROMISED and CLUSTER_STARTING
    Unified health score evaluation for Service Engines, Virtual Services and Pools, changed the default warning level from 90 to 85 and disabled performance and penalty levels by default
    Reworked the Virtual Service ruleset and improved numeric API handling, UTC uptime calculation and retrieval of current inventory values
    Improved Special Agent labels and help texts and enabled Pool collection by default for new rules
    Split graph definitions by component and migrated them to the namespaced Checkmk graphing API
    Removed alert evaluation from Virtual Service checks and marked the standalone Alerts collection option for future removal
    Changed 'Valid until Checkmk version' to 2.6.0b1
    Fixed the parsing error introduced in 0.2.0 for agent sections containing a single or multiple objects
    Fixed the Special Agent class name and Virtual Service status output
    Various stability improvements and code cleanup

2026-07-08 (0.2.0):
    Added Service Engine Disk monitoring (vmware_avi_se_disk)
    Added configurable rulesets for Cloud
    Added configurable monitoring states for VMware Avi Cloud states "Failed" and "In progress"
    Added configurable monitoring state for self-signed certificates
    Added configurable monitoring state for Virtual Services in "Down" state
    Improved data collection by introducing a unified parsing function with better handling of missing API values
    Switched Service Engine interface metrics to built-in Checkmk metrics
    Changed Service Engine CPU monitoring to use the dedicated CPU API endpoint
    Fixed heartbeat agent section format
    Various stability improvements and code cleanup

2026-04-24 (0.1.0):
	init release